<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,951,1367]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,1054,1079]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">Note.</emphasis>
Based upon a single female from 
<collectingCountry box="[671,809,1055,1079]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[820,1106,1054,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="paupera" subSpecies="walthewi">
<emphasis box="[820,1106,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">Halpe paupera walthewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described as a separate subspecies, although only 
<specimenCount box="[497,599,1090,1115]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" type="male">2 males</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[671,796,1090,1115]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" type="female">2 females</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[850,1077,1092,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="paupera" subSpecies="paupera">
<emphasis box="[850,1077,1092,1115]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">H. paupera paupera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from central 
<collectingCountry box="[1263,1358,1090,1115]" name="Vietnam" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
were compared (
<bibRefCitation author="Devyatkin" box="[276,574,1126,1151]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" refString="Devyatkin, A. L. &amp; Monastyrskii, A. L. (2002) Hesperiidae of Vietnam, 12. A further contribution to the Hesperiidae fauna of north and central Vietnam. Atalanta, 33 (1 / 2), 137 - 155." type="journal article" year="2002">Devyatkin 2002: 129–131</bibRefCitation>
). This subspecies has the lower cell spot on the forewing well-developed and two small but sharp spots in space 1b directed to the middle of vein 1 (
<bibRefCitation author="Devyatkin" box="[951,1193,1162,1187]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" refString="Devyatkin, A. L. &amp; Monastyrskii, A. L. (2002) Hesperiidae of Vietnam, 12. A further contribution to the Hesperiidae fauna of north and central Vietnam. Atalanta, 33 (1 / 2), 137 - 155." type="journal article" year="2002">Devyatkin 2002: 131</bibRefCitation>
). However, the photo of the female 
<taxonomicName box="[305,432,1199,1222]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paupera">
<emphasis box="[305,432,1199,1222]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">H. paupera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[501,632,1199,1223]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lo" box="[780,949,1198,1223]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" refString="Lo, P. Y. F. (2005) Hong Kong Butterflies (2 nd edition). Cosmos Books Ltd., Hong Kong, 565 pp." type="book" year="2005">Lo (2005: 123)</bibRefCitation>
is quite different: the lower cell spot on the forewing is reduced and there is no spot in space 1b. Moreover, the male from 
<collectingCountry box="[1085,1220,1235,1259]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lo" box="[1238,1399,1234,1259]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" refString="Lo, P. Y. F. (2005) Hong Kong Butterflies (2 nd edition). Cosmos Books Ltd., Hong Kong, 565 pp." type="book" year="2005">Lo 2005: 123</bibRefCitation>
) is distinguishable from the nominate subspecies by the upper cell spot on the forewing not being elongated, whereas the shape of this spot in the male from 
<collectingRegion box="[591,687,1306,1331]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wang" box="[703,1175,1306,1331]" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" refString="Wang, M. &amp; Tang, D. M. (2012) Butterflies of Guangxi Mao'ershan National Nature Reserve. Guangxi Nationalities Publishing House, Nanning, 194 pp, 113 plates." type="book" year="2012">
Wang &amp; Tang 2012: figs 
<quantity box="[989,1089,1306,1331]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.429" metricValueMax="3.556" metricValueMin="3.302" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" unit="in" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13–14 in</quantity>
pl. 109
</bibRefCitation>
) falls in between those of the 2 subspecies. Thus, 
<taxonomicName box="[447,682,1342,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="paupera" subSpecies="walthewi">
<emphasis box="[447,682,1342,1367]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">H. paupera walthewi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is likely a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[946,1073,1343,1366]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Halpe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paupera">
<emphasis box="[946,1073,1343,1366]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="321">H. paupera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
